                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nOxybutynin is an antispasmodic used to relieve symptoms of urinary urgency, frequency, nocturia, and incontinence in clients with uninhibited or reflex neurogenic bladder. Expected effects include improved urinary control and decreased urinary frequency, incontinence, and nocturia. The questions in the remaining options are unrelated to the use of this medication.",
