                        "content": "The home health nurse has been discussing interventions to prevent constipation in a client with multiple sclerosis. The nurse determines that the client is using the information most effectively if the client reports which action?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nTo manage constipation, the client needs to take in a high-fiber diet, bulk formers, and stool softeners. A fluid intake of 2000 mL/day is recommended. The client needs to initiate a bowel movement on an every-other-day basis and would sit on the toilet or commode. This would be done approximately 45 minutes after the largest meal of the day to take advantage of the gastrocolic reflex. A glycerin suppository, bisacodyl suppository, or digital stimulation may be used to initiate the process. Laxatives and enemas would be avoided whenever possible because they lead to dependence.",
                        "id": "2c5fddeef8804f68bfff3780e1e72029",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "21462b28bd944fc2abcea5a4260eaa9f",
                                "content": "Inability to care for self"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b01d7bbd8c6343d3a1e2ce8d4b6f0a8e",
                                "content": "Interruption in skin integrity"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "04cb2ca7b75d4d439f1123e7da909903",
                                "content": "Interruption in physical mobility"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "2d7a6ecdb83a4d89866c0b3e76b5fd48",
                                "content": "Inability to perform daily activities"
