                        "content": "A client with multiple sclerosis is experiencing muscle weakness, spasticity, and an ataxic gait. On the basis of this information, the nurse would include which client problem in the plan of care?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nMultiple sclerosis is a chronic, nonprogressive, noncontagious degenerative disease of the central nervous system characterized by demyelination of the neurons. Interruption in physical mobility is most appropriate for the client with multiple sclerosis experiencing muscle weakness, spasticity, and ataxic gait. The remaining options are not related to the data in the question.",
                        "id": "5cc1500e32c1404b8d31094dd01d6340",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9dd181fedc0247918ea1f4cd265d05f6",
                                "content": "400 to 500 mL with each meal and 500 to 600 mL in the evening before bedtime"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e8af77f1acd74a049f67ebc037e26666",
                                "content": "400 to 500 mL with each meal and additional fluids in the morning but not after midday"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "0694ba4a15664cc5ab6a5075704f86a5",
                                "content": "400 to 500 mL with each meal, with all extra fluid concentrated in the afternoon and evening"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b28bf222582f4b5bb36ce0ff916e4eb4",
                                "content": "400 to 500 mL with each meal and 200 to 250 mL at midmorning, midafternoon, and late afternoon"
